  <Docs>
    <summary>Specifies how a rotation occurs with one point of user input.</summary>
    <remarks>
      <format type="text/markdown"><![CDATA[  
  
## Remarks  
 The <xref:System.Windows.Input.ManipulationStartingEventArgs.Pivot%2A?displayProperty=nameWithType> property is a <xref:System.Windows.Input.ManipulationPivot>. When you set <xref:System.Windows.Input.ManipulationStartingEventArgs.Pivot%2A> in an event handler for the <xref:System.Windows.UIElement.ManipulationStarting> event, the manipulation will contain rotation data when the user uses one finger during a manipulation.  This is to simulate real-world situations where you can use one finger to rotate an object, such as a piece of paper on a table.  If the <xref:System.Windows.Input.ManipulationStartingEventArgs.Pivot%2A> is `null`, the user must use two fingers to cause rotation.  
  
   
  
